				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Has anyone had this happen to them in an AE kite?<a name="49160"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 29 04 7:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've noticed it in PoD w/ ALL of the flies chasing me.  
<br />

<br />
When I swarm, I pull all of the flies.  Almost 20 vetri flies, the occasional scaevian or senguian if it's up in a vetri's place, 5 or more tachnicians, and all of the tsetsian flies.  I'm not sure of amout of opening damage they can do, but it's like 10k or so because if I start the swarm kite off by charming a tsetsian (which has just about 10k hps), it will go down as soon as the other mobs find it.
<br />

<br />
What's odd, though, is that while pulling, if I get stunned, I'll take like 37 damage, all of the rest of the mobs will catch up, but then they'll just stand there.  If I get hit after they're rounded up, though, I turn into a pile of kitty goo.  
<br />

<br />
So, I believe Reilna is correct - if they're out of melee range (which is the case while pulling, usually, but not after the tight circles start), the others won't swing.
<br />

<br />
Good observation.</span></td>
