			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Has anyone had this happen to them in an AE kite?<a name="50532"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 7 04 1:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This one I can answer. IF you were in the middle of a turn, however slight, when stunned you'll go into a spin and have to gauge which way to run in order to escape death. 
<br />

<br />
For example, if you were running straight and get stunned while only holding the forward movement button you will not spin but stand in place. If you were holding down forward button and a left/right key as you would while turning when you get stunned, you will make turns in that direction. The speed that you turn at can also be variable, but to the best of my knowledge the variation is due to how and how many mobs stun/hit you.
<br />

<br />
The best way to survive such a hit is to try to guess at which point you will break out of stun in your spin and try to move in a direction most favorable to survival. Most of the time I end up having to run backwards. Sometimes I end up sideways and have very little chance of surviving.
<br />

<br />
The reasons you get knocked out of melee range when stunned is because the mobs are so tightly packed its not one mob bashing you but a collection of 10-15 mobs bashing you and maybe getting a hit in. Once the first 6 or 7 bashes land, you are officially out of melee range usually simply due to knockback effect of the bash. Since you are technically stunned(or short duration mezzed) and are out of melee range, mobs dont move into melee range to beat you further. The orientation, spin/no-spin, action of your character is based on the direction you are moving at the time you get smacked.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

"Be a bard's bard!"</span></td>
